==English==

===Pronunciation===
*băn'di, /ˈbændi/, /<tt>"b{ndi</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ændi|Rhymes: -ændi]]

===Etymology 1===
{{MF.}} from ''[[bander]]''

===Verb===
'''to bandy'''
#To give and [[receive]] [[reciprocally]]; to [[exchange]]; as "to ''bandy words'' (with sb.)".
#To use or [[pass]] about [[casually]]; as "to have one's name ''bandied about'' (or ''around'')".

===Etymology 2===
From {{sco}} ''bandy''.

[[category:Scots derivations]]

===Adjective===
'''bandy'''
#[[Bowlegged]], or [[bending]] outward at the [[knees]]; as in [[bandy legged]].

===Etymology 3===
Possibly from the {{cy}} word ''bandy'' most likeley derived from the [[Teutonic]] word ''bandja'' (a curbed stick).

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''bandy'''
#A British winter sport related to [[ice hockey]].

